               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> ASHWELLTHORPE. Letters of confirmation from <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename>, the
               prior</persName>, and <orgName key="org_104033">convent of the cathedral church of Norwich</orgName> to 
               <persName>sir <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Thorpe</surname>, kt.</persName>, for
               the foundation of a chantry within the church of <placeName key="place_104185">Asshewellethorp</placeName>, containing a
               recital of (1) confirmation by <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, bp. of <placeName type="diocese" role="bishop" key="place_101090">Norwich</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               (2) letters patent of <persName>King Edward II</persName> dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_100060">Westminster</placeName>, 15 Dec., 5 of his reign, 
               (3) charter of <persName>sir <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Thorp</surname>, kt.</persName>, granting 
               a messuage croft and 63s. 4d. annual rents in the village of
               <placeName key="place_104185">Asshewellethorpe</placeName> for the foundation of the same chantry, 
               (4) grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Claveryngg</surname>, lord of <placeName role="lord" key="place_104377">Horsford</placeName>
                        </persName>, for the assignment of the said messuage and rents, 
               (5) grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Thorp</surname>, rector of the church of <placeName role="rector" key="place_104185">All Saints, Asshewellethorpe</placeName>
                        </persName>, confirming the donation of his brother. 
               Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_104458">Norwich</placeName>, 10 Kl. July, <origDate when="1316">1316</origDate>.</p>
                  </msItem>
